 stepchildren","body":"Between 1840 and 1850 Amanda remarried — to Judge Joseph Hayward of Vermont (1796-1865). Hayward already had three children from his prior marriage (Asaph, Josephine, and Benjamin); they were Amanda's stepchildren, not her own biological children. The blended Wilder-Hayward household took shape across the 1840s, with Amanda raising her two Wilder children alongside her three Hayward stepchildren."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Daughter Marion married into Drake family","body":"Amanda's daughter Marion Eliza Wilder (born 1836) eventually married Drake — establishing the Wilder-Drake line that descended from the Hooker connection through Amanda's mother Lucinda Murray. Amanda's son Henry Harrison Wilder served as a private in the Civil War."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born Addison County VT 1810, died Vermont 1887","body":"Amanda Murray was born April 30, 1810 in Addison County Vermont and died December 9, 1887 in Vermont at age seventy-seven. Her two marriages with their distinct biological-vs-step parentage have been cross-checked against source records to establish the marriage order and parentage definitively."}],"slug":"amanda-hayward-1810"},"HD3215":{"id":"HD3215","has_descendants_documented":false,"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true},"birth":{"year":1812,"month":2,"day":19,"city":"Addison","county":"Addison County","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1885,"month":3,"day":6,"city":"Middlebury","county":"Addison County","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"X01941","mother_id":"HD0435"},"marriages":[],"tags":[],"sources":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cro